ef816dfe-e9a7-4455-8bd6-5f6c340eaab4.001cb902-f00c-4259-be56-d5786ea48a1c.prompt=Should the operation check subfolders? WARNING this may be very slow ef816dfe-e9a7-4455-8bd6-5f6c340eaab4.20b84057-fd5e-417a-88e8-f4ad16c4eb52.description=
Executes an Expression (e.x value1 \=\= value2)

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the value to threshold with
value2 - the threshold to threshold against
operator - (\=\=, \!\=,  >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold
okstring - string to push into returnResult if the threshold has not been passed
failedstring - string to push into the returnResult if the threshold has been passed

Responses\:
true - the expression is true
fales - the expression is false
ef816dfe-e9a7-4455-8bd6-5f6c340eaab4.3e6426f2-087b-4b40-8f27-8d51652420f8.description=Iterates through a list of values.If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration.. ef816dfe-e9a7-4455-8bd6-5f6c340eaab4.3f18448d-e0bc-4dea-95a1-7eaef7ed203e.description=
Adds a value into the global context (available to all parent and child flows)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];

ef816dfe-e9a7-4455-8bd6-5f6c340eaab4.a7dc3b9b-a2d8-4f29-bdeb-3cefa7a84365.description= 
Compares a files size to a given threshold.

Input Parameters\:
source - the file to read
Threshold - the threshold to compare the file size to (in bytes).
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The file probably could not be found.
greater than	- The file's size is larger than the threshold.
less than		- The file's size is smaller than the threshold.
equal to		- The file's size is the same as the threshold.

Extra Results\:
size			- The file's size in bytes.
ef816dfe-e9a7-4455-8bd6-5f6c340eaab4.d5d76188-7619-4a23-af7d-201a7791e9af.description= 
Gets a list of files and folders in a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - the directory to check
delimiter - A delimiter to put between files and folders in the directory.
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

returns\:
The children of the path.

Extra Results\:
count - the number of children.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path probably could not be found, or was a file.
success			- The operation succeeded.
ef816dfe-e9a7-4455-8bd6-5f6c340eaab4.description=
Goes through a windows directory and returns the largest file.

Inputs\:
Source - The source directory.
user - the username to run as.
password - password for user.
recursive - whether to recurse through sub directories.

Responses\:
success - operation completed.
failure - something went wrong.
ef816dfe-e9a7-4455-8bd6-5f6c340eaab4.e2e312c1-1f84-416a-a61b-f264fa343ae3.description= 
Checks to see if a path points to a directory.

Input Parameters\:
source - the path to check
username - username to use when reading.
password - password to use when reading.

Responses\:
failure			- the operation failed. The path does not point to a directory.
success			- The operation succeeded.
flow.name: Get Largest File
